init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You and the rest of the Lost Generations are sent to a facility to die.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: You and the rest of the Lost Generations are sent to a facility to die.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The government tries to force people to work, but it's not working.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you don't work, you don't get any social security or Medicare.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And if you don't work, you don't get to vote.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The plan works, but not in the way the government expected.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The government tries to make it harder to get disability, but the lawyers just get better at their jobs.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Soon, half the country is on disability.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So what's the government to do?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And there's no more crime, because no one wants to commit it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So the government decides to do what it should have done in the first place: it gives the drug to everyone.
